# How much will I earn with my GPU?
You won’t know until you try it out for yourself. The closest to making an educated guess would be to see which GPU’s are currently on the subnet here: https://opencompute.streamlit.app/ and have a look at what other miners are earning on sn27 here: https://x.taostats.io/subnet/27

# Do I get my registration fee back?
No, once you pay the fee (recycle), you will not get it back and if you get deregistered you will need to pay the fee to register again.

# How do I get deregistered?
There is an element of competitiveness inherent in all subnets. To remain registered, your miner must be competitive in hash completion times. We have created a benchmark script for you to test your miner before registering.
https://github.com/neuralinternet/compute-subnet/blob/main/test-scripts/benchmark.py

# What is the testnet UID?
15. We highly suggest testing your setup on testnet (and doing the benchmark test) before registering on main net.

# How long is immunity?
9000 blocks which is roughly 30 hours

# Can I run a miner with more than 1 GPU?
Multigpu is enabled, however rewards are not linear to the amount of GPU’s your machine has.

# I am having trouble with Runpod, Vast.ai, Tensordock etc. what should I do?
Currently dockerized instances cannot be used on this subnet. You will need a virtual machine or bare metal with docker installed.

# How do I resolve this error? `Error while fetching server API version: Not supported URL scheme http+docker`

`pip install requests==2.30`

# I am getting this error:`wandb init failed: It appears that you do not have permission to access the requested resource. Please reach out to the project owner to grant you access. If you have the correct permissions, verify that there are no issues with your networking setup.(Error 403: Forbidden)`

This is a known issue on wandb’s side and the team are actively working with them to resolve it. Not having access to wandb will affect your incentive as validators use it to verify your machine’s specs. If you are considering registering right now, we suggest holding off until this issue is resolved.

Hey @Nautilus [τ, ג]  @lucian [τ, נ] SN41  regarding the issue I had with wand permissions, I believe I know where the problem is. I need your support to confirm this. Neither me nor my provider made any change and the issue is now solved with all my miners. My guess is that when the miner is deregistered , pm2 continues resetting the miner and wandb is logged multiple times... until wandb blocks the IP due to multiple logins after long time.
